\begin_layout Subsubsection
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sub:single-pulse-TMS"

\end_inset

Single-pulse TMS
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This technique has been developed as a diagnostic method for evaluation
 of cortico-spinal pathway.
 During stimulation of the motor cortex with single magnetic pulses of sufficien
t intensity an acute depolarisation of whole population of neurons occurs.
 It is followed by excitation of neuronal pathways from brain through the
 spinal cord to the muscles, resulting in measurable motor evoked potentials
 (MEP).
 This technique has been also used for evaluation of changes in excitability
 of cortical neurons resulting from application of different transcranial
 stimulation methods.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "sub:rTMS"

\end_inset

Repetitive TMS
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Although single-pulse TMS has been developed as a diagnostic tool, it has
 been observed that the magnetic pulses have an long term neuromodulation
 effect.
 This lead to a development of more powerful TMS generators capable of delivery
 of multiple pulses within short time -- the rTMS.
 Empirically, rTMS has been further subdivided to 
\emph on
low-
\emph default
 (rates below 1
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

Hz) and 
\emph on
high-frequency rTMS
\emph default
 (rates above 5
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

Hz).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Experimental evidence has revealed that rTMS with repetition rates below
 1
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

Hz causes cortical inhibition and on the other hand rTMS trains above 5
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

Hz have opposite effect.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In order to increase efficiency of the high-frequency rTMS a repeated individual
 pulses have been substituted with groups of pulses, or — the burts.
 In a variant of rTMS, a theta-burst stimulation (TBS), the bursts of two
 or more pulses with intra-burst rate up to 50
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

Hz and inter-burst frequency of approximately 5
\begin_inset space ~
\end_inset

Hz are used.
 Although there is an evidence about increased efficiency, concerns about
 safety of the method arose.
 One of the limitations of current technology is that rTMS does not affect
 the deeper structures of the brain, but it is known that rTMS significantly
 involved in changing the perception of pain.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
According to recent studies 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Rokyta2014"

\end_inset

, this method is able to induce changes in the central nervous system at
 the cellular level including changes at ionic and metabolic level.
 Therapeutic effects were confirmed in the literature of psychiatric disorders
 such as depression, acute mania, bipolar disorder, panic attacks, hallucination
s, obsessive states, schizophrenia, catatonia or post-traumatic stress disorder
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "Rokyta2012b"

\end_inset

